#### **Phase 3: Atomic Marker Detection** 
```go
// Regex-based detection with performance optimization
func detectAtomicMarkers(text string, rules []Rule) []Marker {
    markers := make([]Marker, 0, 100)
    
    for _, rule := range rules {
        // Use pre-compiled regex for performance 
        matches := rule.regex.FindAllStringIndex(text, -1)
        for _, match := range matches {
            markers = append(markers, Marker{
                Type:       rule.Type,
                TextSpan:   text[match[0]:match[1]],
                Start:      match[0],
                End:        match[1],
                Confidence: rule.Weight,
                RuleID:     rule.ID,
            })
        }
    }
    
    // Stable sort by position
    sort.SliceStable(markers, func(i, j int) bool {
        return markers[i].Start < markers[j].Start
    })
    
    return markers
}
```

#### **Phase 4-5: Composite & Semantic Analysis**
- Implement context window builder using sentence boundaries
- Create rule-based NER using pattern dictionaries
- Build semantic proximity analyzer using predefined networks
- Add logical expression interpreter for complex rules

